            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]<strong> </span>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken breast portions</strong> and most of the<strong> sliced garlic</strong> (save some for later!) and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden</p><p>Add a couple of splashes of <strong>water</strong> to the pan and cover with a lid, then cook for a further 12-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1655806818453-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1655806818453-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1655806818453-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1655806818453-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1655806818453-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add <strong>half </strong>of the <strong>diced avocado </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), most<strong> </strong>of the <strong>chopped basil</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and the <strong>reserved sliced</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> (not a big garlic fan? Try using less!) to a <strong>food processor</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> </strong>juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong>, 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>avo dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1655806819863-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1655806819863-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1655806819863-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1655806819863-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1655806819863-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and add to a large bowl with the<strong> tomato wedges</strong>, <strong>remaining diced avocado</strong> and <strong>croutons</strong>, season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Give it a gentle mix up – this is your <strong>salad</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1655806825396-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1655806825396-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1655806825396-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1655806825396-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1655806825396-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>cooked chicken</strong> to a clean board and slice finely</p><p>Serve the<strong> sliced</strong> <strong>chicken </strong>over the <strong>salad</strong> and drizzle the <strong>avo dressing</strong> all over</p><p>Garnish with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong>, the <strong>remaining basil </strong>and a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
